org.numenta.nupic.network.sensor

Class FileSensor

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.numenta.nupic.network.sensor.FileSensor
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, Persistable, Sensor<java.io.File>

    public class FileSensor
extends java.lang.Object
implements Sensor<java.io.File>, java.io.Serializable
    Default implementation of a Sensor for inputting data from a file. All Sensors represent the bottom-most level of any given Network. Sensors are used to connect to a data source and feed data into the Network, therefore there are no nodes beneath them or which precede them within the Network hierarchy, in terms of data flow. In fact, a Sensor will throw an Exception if an attempt to connect another node to the input of a node containing a Sensor is made.
    Author:
    David Ray
    See Also:
    SensorFactory, Sensor.create(SensorFactory, SensorParams), Serialized Form
